> Need to know more about the how the markets function, the players, the

> regulators and today's hot topic?

> Then, check-out the cost-effective courses being offered by the Institute

> for Financial Markets. The IFM, established in 1989, is a nonprofit

> foundation and leading educational and information institute serving the

> financial services industry. Programs are directed to market-users,

> journalists, academics, congressional staffers, agency personnel and those

> who develop and implement public policy.

>

>

> Futures and Options Seminar

> Feb. 25 & 26 - Washington DC

> Mar. 18 & 19 - New York City

> This comprehensive two-day training session is ideal for new hires, those

> requiring a more in depth knowledge about futures and options. The seminar

> provides a foundation in the fundamentals of futures and options market

> theory and practice. (The class also is ideal Series 3 candidates seeking

> market knowledge.) This seminar price of $525 includes two text books and

> PassMaster a tutorial software program.

>

>

> An Introduction to Security Futures

> Mar. 20 - New York City

> Apr. 23 - New York City

> It's the new hot topic! Security Futures, once a banned product, will

> begin trading later this year. This half-day course presents an overview

> of security futures and the underlying cash markets including the

> requirements for trading and offering these innovative products. The class

> price is only $225.

> What are security futures? Click here

> http://www.theifm.org/index.cfm?inc=securityFutures/securityFutures.inc.

>

>

> For more information please call  202.223.1528 or visit our web site at

> www.theIFM.org . For program details please click on the following direct

> link  http://www.theifm.org/index.cfm?inc=eventsCalendar.inc . Multiple

> attendees and government discounts are available. Class size is limited to

> promote an interactive and productive learning environment, so please

> respond now to reserve your seat!

>

